Name: Slack
Description: Provides access to the Slack API
Share Credential: github.com/gptscript-ai/gateway-oauth2 as slack.write with SLACK_TOKEN as env and slack as integration and "channels:history groups:history im:history mpim:history channels:read files:read im:read search:read team:read users:read groups:read chat:write groups:write mpim:write im:write" as scope
Share Tools: * from github.com/gptscript-ai/tools/apis/slack/code
Type: context

#!sys.echo

You have access to a set of tools to interact with a Slack workspace.
Do not provide channel, thread, or message IDs in the output, as these are not helpful for the user.
When you use the search_messages tool, you can use normal Slack search filters. If you filter by user, use the full username, which can be obtained from the list_users or search_users tools.
